#: ../../B/bells-and-whistles.rst:5
msgid "bells and whistles"
msgstr "bells and whistles"

#: ../../B/bells-and-whistles.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/bells-and-whistles.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] Features added to a program or system to make it more "
":ref:`flavorful` from a hacker's point of view, without necessarily adding "
"to its utility for its primary function. Distinguished from :ref:`chrome`\\,"
" which is intended to attract users. \"Now that we've got the basic program "
"working, let's go back and add some bells and whistles.\" No one seems to "
"know what distinguishes a bell from a whistle. The recognized emphatic form "
"is \"bells, whistles, and gongs\"."
msgstr ""
"[一般的]主要な機能の実用性を必ずしも高めることなく、ハッカーの観点からより\\ :ref:`flavorful`\\ "
"にするためにプログラムやシステムに加えられる機能。ユーザーを引きつけることを意図した\\ :ref:`chrome`\\ "
"とは区別される。「基本プログラムが動くようになったから、戻ってbells and "
"whistlesをいくつか加えよう」。bell(鈴)とwhistle(笛)を何が区別するのかは、誰も知らないようだ。認知された強調形は「bells, "
"whistles, and gongs(鈴、笛、銅鑼)」である。"

#: ../../B/bells-and-whistles.rst:15
msgid ""
"It used to be thought that this term derived from the toyboxes on theater "
"organs. However, the \"and gongs\" strongly suggests a different origin, at "
"sea. Before powered horns, ships routinely used bells, whistles, and gongs "
"to signal each other over longer distances than voice can carry."
msgstr ""
"かつてこの用語は、劇場用オルガンのtoybox(効果音装置)に由来すると考えられていた。しかし「and "
"gongs」は、海という別の起源を強く示唆する。動力式の汽笛が登場する前、船は声の届く範囲より遠くで互いに信号を送り合うのに、鈴・笛・銅鑼を日常的に使っていた。"

#: ../../B/bells-and-whistles.rst:23
msgid "Sometimes ‘trouble’ is spelled        :ref:`bells-and-whistles`\\..."
msgstr "‘trouble(やっかいごと)’は\\ :ref:`bells-and-whistles`\\ と綴られることもある……"

